In the next video, what I'm
going to do is give you a

00:04:48.770 --> 00:04:53.780
little bit more intuition
for what exactly does

00:04:53.780 --> 00:04:54.780
this thing mean?

00:04:54.780 --> 00:04:57.560
And how does it change
depending on different

00:04:57.560 --> 00:04:58.540
parameterizations.

